        "description": "Company Description\n\nWe are a global company, a leader in information services, known in the rest of the world as Experian. In life’s major moments—such as buying a car, sending a child to college, or even starting and growing a business—we are there to empower consumers and clients to manage their data with confidence.\n\nWe have more than 20,000 people operating in over 44 countries; and by investing in them, in technology, and in innovation, we can help businesses transform and communities thrive, enabling more people to feel included in the opportunities available. This is how we deliver on our purpose every day: to create a better future.\n\nCome explore an unexpected world with us.\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are looking for an Infrastructure & DevOps Engineer to help build, automate, and maintain reliable, secure, and scalable infrastructure across hybrid-cloud and on‑premise environments. You will contribute to the evolution of our automation ecosystem, support global DevOps platforms, and strengthen operational excellence through engineering best practices.\n\n🛠️ Your Key Responsibilities\n\nDesign, develop, implement, and support infrastructure automation solutions using Infrastructure as Code and configuration management tools for consistent, scalable provisioning across hybrid cloud and on‑prem environments.Provide operational support for global DevOps and self‑service automation platforms such as Ansible Tower and private cloud automation services, ensuring availability, performance, and adherence to operational standards.Implement and maintain infrastructure security controls, including OS hardening, patching, and secure configurations.Identify manual or repetitive operational processes and develop automation solutions, maintaining and refactoring existing codebases.Collaborate with cross‑functional teams, follow change management and coding standards, and produce clear documentation to support team alignment and knowledge sharing.Ensure the availability and reliability of production servers and applications by participating in on‑call rotations, performing root cause analysis, and executing service restoration activities.\n\nQualifications\n\n🎯 What we expect from you\n\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Systems, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.Experience with DevOps and infrastructure automation in enterprise environments.Administration of Linux (Red Hat, SUSE) and Windows Server.Knowledge of Infrastructure as Code and automation tools: Ansible, Terraform.Scripting/programming: Bash, PowerShell, YAML, Python.Experience with CI/CD tools (e.g., Jenkins).Familiarity with cloud platforms: AWS, Azure, GCP.Experience with containerization and orchestration technologies.Skills in server provisioning, patching, and OS security hardening.Experience with monitoring, performance tuning, and troubleshooting.Knowledge of version control systems (Git, Bitbucket).Experience working with Agile (Scrum) and ITIL‑based operational processes.Strong analytical, problem‑solving, and documentation skills.+ Advanced English and availability to travel to São Carlos/SP when need it.\n\n⭐ Nice to have\n\nRelevant DevOps, automation, or cloud certifications (preferred).\n\nAdditional Information\n\nAt Serasa Experian, we believe that diversity is essential for a healthier and more innovative work environment, where everyone can share experiences and express their ideas. That’s why we promote several initiatives to support inclusive recruitment and the professional development of our people.\n\nWe also have our affinity groups, created to empower and support individuals from underrepresented groups: ExperianPride (LGBTQIAPN+ community), Ubuntu (racial equity), Women in Experian (gender equity), Aspire (people with disabilities), and Connecting Generations (generations).\n\nCome be part of this transformation!\n\nExperian Careers - Creating a better tomorrow together\n\nFind out what its like to work for Experian by clicking here",
